  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposal fails to promote sustainable modes of transport, due to the excessive car parking provision, and result in conditions prejudicial to the free flow and safety of pedestrian and vehicular movements, due to the unnecessarily introduction of a second vehicle access, removal of an on-street CPZ car parking bay, and insufficient pedestrian access arrangements. Therefore the proposal would be contrary to London Plan policy T6.1 and Local Plan policy EC2 and the Council's adopted Residential Crossover and Off-Street Parking Policy.",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposal fails to provide sufficient soft landscaping, unnecessarily removes mature trees, and features inappropriate hardstanding materials, which would harm the character of the surrounding area contrary to Local Plan policy SC7 and GB7 and the Hounslow Character, Sustainability and Design Codes (SPD), and the Council's Residential Crossover and Off-Street Parking policy."
